HEADWORD: Luxullianite
<hw>Lux*ul"li*an*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called
from <ets>Luxullian</ets>, in Cornwall.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
kind of granite from Luxullian, Cornwall, characterized by the presence
of radiating groups of minute tourmaline crystals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

